12/10/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The home of a Kosovo Serb near Gjilan/Gnjilane in eastern Kosovo was attacked on Saturday (October 10th), police announced. The hand grenade lobbed at the home of Milorad Todorovic caused no injuries. Todorovic is an official with the Democratic Party of Serbia. About 30 Serb families live together with 100 Albanian families in the village of Cernica. (Koha Ditore, Express - 12/10/09; B92 - 11/10/09)
